cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this repository, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "GSC (Gravitational Structural Collapse)"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Baev"
    given-names: "Dimitar"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0009-7812-9203"
    affiliation: "Monster Cleaning Ltd. — https://monstercleaning.com"
repository-code: "https://github.com/monstercleaning/gsc"
url: "https://github.com/monstercleaning/gsc"
license: "MIT"
abstract: >
  An open-source pre-registration reproducibility stack demonstrated on a
  scale-covariant cosmology framework. The stack combines deterministic
  computational pipelines, cryptographically-signed numerical predictions, and
  a layered claim hierarchy (kinematic → phenomenological → ansatz →
  speculative extensions) to make speculative model-building falsifiable in
  operational practice. Developed and audited via multi-LLM iterative
  hostile-review cycles. The cosmology framework itself serves as a working
  case study; the methodology is the primary contribution.
keywords:
  - cosmology
  - scale-covariant
  - renormalization group
  - dark energy
  - reproducibility
  - pre-registration
  - falsification
  - AI-assisted research
  - multi-LLM peer review
